<span class="header1">BUSINESS & ENVIRONMENT</span>
<p>The occupations in this field protect, manage, or research the
environment. If the environment is one of your interests, you might
want to consider the occupations in this field. Here are three
examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Waste Management
Technician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AC/43020.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Waste Management
Technician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Manufacturing processes can create dangerous
waste materials.  If you become a waste management technician, you
might help to remove chemical or nuclear wastes created by these
processes.  You would wear protective clothing. You would work with
equipment designed to remove toxic waste from the water and
soil.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma to become a waste
management technician. You would also participate in a training
program offered by your company.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of waste management
technicians was $44,190 in May 2016.
</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Park Ranger</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/C585042.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Park Ranger" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A park ranger makes sure that visitors and
wildlife are safe in state and national parks. As a park ranger, you
would patrol the park.  You would also collect fees, provide
information about the park, and enforce park rules and
regulations.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Workers in this occupation need, at a minimum, a
bachelor's degree in forestry, environmntal science, range
management, or a related discipline.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of park rangers was
$60,610 in May 2016. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Forestry Technician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CF/43168.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Forestry Technician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A forestry technician works to allow people to
visit and use our forests, and to protect the environment. If you
become a forestry technician, you might plan and oversee forest
operations. These include logging, tree planting, water regulation,
and wildlife management. You might also collect information for
research and oversee work crews. This is not an easy job. You must
be willing to work hard and be outside in all kinds of weather.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>To become a forestry technician, you need a
bachelor's degree from one of the 47 schools that specialize in
forestry.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of forestry technicians
was $58,700 in May 2016.
</blockquote>

